WEBVTT

00:05.673 --> 00:10.344
CHRIS ROCK:
When I was 16, I crossed a
major milestone for teenagers.

00:10.378 --> 00:14.082
I finally got
my driver's license.

00:14.115 --> 00:15.783
* Here in my car...

00:15.816 --> 00:17.385
The difference
between taking the bus

00:17.418 --> 00:19.753
and being able to drive
was obvious.

00:19.787 --> 00:21.655
Hey, Tasha, I'm going
down to Alby Square.

00:21.689 --> 00:23.724
You want to come?
Are you taking the bus?

00:23.757 --> 00:25.459
Yeah.
No.

00:25.493 --> 00:26.794
Did I mention I have
a two

00:26.827 --> 00:29.263
Hey, Tasha, I'm going
down to Alby Square.

00:29.297 --> 00:30.431
You want to come?
Yeah.

00:30.464 --> 00:31.532
I was just about to go there.

00:33.101 --> 00:34.535
Bye, Chris.
See you downtown.

00:42.643 --> 00:44.412
Back home at dinner,
the only thing

00:44.445 --> 00:46.380
I was hungry for was a car.

00:46.414 --> 00:47.715
Boy, this is
not a library.

00:47.748 --> 00:49.617
If it was, you'd be quiet.

00:49.650 --> 00:52.553
I'm sorry-- I'm looking
for a good deal on a used car.

00:52.586 --> 00:54.355
A car?

00:54.388 --> 00:56.490
Yeah. Since I have my license,
I figured I should have a car.

00:56.524 --> 00:57.425
Did you figure

00:57.458 --> 00:58.826
I would tell you you were crazy?

00:58.859 --> 01:00.261
If Chris gets a car,

01:00.294 --> 01:02.263
can I have a football helmet?
For what?

01:02.296 --> 01:04.332
Because I don't want to be
on the street unprotected.

01:04.365 --> 01:05.533
I think you should get

01:05.566 --> 01:06.534
a Suzuki Samurai.

01:06.567 --> 01:07.568
That's because he thought

01:07.601 --> 01:08.869
the car came with a sword.

01:08.902 --> 01:10.571
But if you don't
get a Samurai,

01:10.604 --> 01:11.672
you should get a Audi 5000.

01:11.705 --> 01:13.307
That way, when
you leave a place,

01:13.341 --> 01:14.575
you're, like,
"Yo, I'm Audi 5000,

01:14.608 --> 01:16.544
and then you'd be in one--
that'd be cool.

01:16.577 --> 01:17.411
Chris is
not getting

01:17.445 --> 01:19.280
a car.
Come on, Ma,

01:19.313 --> 01:21.115
I saved up $300,
I got my license--

01:21.149 --> 01:22.250
what else do I need?

01:22.283 --> 01:23.351
My permission.

01:23.384 --> 01:25.753
$300? That's
a lot of dollars.

01:25.786 --> 01:27.355
300, to be exact.

01:27.388 --> 01:28.656
If he's old enough to save up

01:28.689 --> 01:30.224
that kind of money,
he's old enough

01:30.258 --> 01:31.359
to spend it
on what he wants.

01:31.392 --> 01:34.528
It's a good thing I was
too young for strip clubs.

01:46.840 --> 01:48.909
* Ah, make it funky now.

